The faces I make when someone says the market will crash. 🫠 Dubious at best - here’s why:

🤔Do y’all remember the excess housing in 2008 that caused values to plummet? How much inventory do you think we have right now? I’ll give you a hint: not enough for the demand, especially in San Diego. 📉

👀Do you know what the government’s response was for all those sub-prime loans and lax lending practices? A whole lot of regulations, making the qualification process extensive but thorough. Ability to repay is the key to getting a home 🏡

👉🏽Fact: We are at record lows for foreclosures. Your average homeowner is not in distress - they’re sitting on mountains of equity and have strong credit. This is a huge difference between 2008 and now, due to the qualifying process. 👏🏽

✍🏽At the end of the day you can try to time the market all you want… I believe that the best time to buy is largely dependent upon your stability and situation. But also, do the math on the money you’ve lost while renting💸:
1️⃣ Is renting from someone else earning you equity? 
2️⃣ Can you pull from those funds or are they gone? 
3️⃣ And lastly what is the one, guaranteed thing we’ve seen in San Diego with rent? It increases year over year due to consistent demand.

📲Let’s chat about your homeownership goals, here to help educate and empower future homeowners!

I’ve found happiness in my personal and professional life, and when I smile now, it’s genuine. 🌊 Flood Insurance: Let’s talk about it: it’s intended to protect & cover losses directly caused by flooding (but typically not mold, #FYI) 🌧️ As most of San Diego is flooding, bringing up the importance of flood insurance coverage seems… crucial. 🫠 SanDiego.gov has a direct link to FEMA’s “Special Flood Hazard Areas” which are used by mortgage lenders to help protect you and the property in case of an unfortunate flood event. 😬 Like today. 🌧️

👀 #GoodNews: As a resident of the City of San Diego, those who are required to purchase flood insurance may be eligible to receive subsidized flood insurance through the national flood insurance program! 🥳

📍The NFIP is a government program that is only available in the cities that actively comply with FEMA’s floodplain management standards. ✅ Luckily, the City of San Diego renewed its compliance with FEMA in December 2019! 💪🏽 Stay dry, everyone! 😮‍💨
